Rating: 4
Super flavorful and everyone loved it. Made a batch for a dinner for 4 and thought I'd have leftovers. Yeah, right! I used spicy chicken italian sausage from Trader Joes, and it was wonderful. I added toasted pecans instead of walnuts and a handful of chopped dried cranberries. Also, to get the fennel to soften, I added a few tablespoons of water to the onion/fennel mixture after it had sauteed for a bit and covered it to let the steam soften the fennel. Served with pheasant (my friend bird hunts)and the brussels sprouts with shallots and mustard seeds from this site.

